Help

Shortcuts

Editor

ctrl + return or cmd + return : submit line to server

ctrl + alt + return or cmd + alt + return : submit all to server

ctrl + backspace or cmd + backspace : clear current line

ctrl + / or cmd + / : comment/uncomment current line

ctrl + s or cmd + s : save editor content to local storage

ctrl + shift + s or cmd + shift + s : save editor content externally


Messages

ctrl + alt : hide message

ctrl + shift : show last message again (will not close automatically)


Popup Windows

alt + c : show chart

alt + k : show code.kx.com

alt + h : show help

alt + ,  : show settings


Other

esc : close web socket connection or close popup

shift + esc : open web socket connection

shift + backspace : clear local storage


Extra Information

You may find out more at http://carlosbutler.com/Webstudio/#ei. There you will find detailed information on Webstudio and how to submit bugs and feedback.

Settings

Servers

  • Add server
  • Remove server

Splash Screen

  • - Permanently disable splash screen (normally shows once per day).

Layout

  • You can select either a top-bottom (portrait) layout or side-by-side (landscape) layout.
  • You may choose how many extra buttons are displayed.


NOTE: You will need to refresh the browser to apply the layout settings.

Check For Updates

  • To check for updates you must be connected to a Q server that has an Internet connection.
  • Check for updates

Maximum Return Size

  • If the browser takes too long rendering large tables, it is possible to limit the maximum data received.
    As an estimate, an OHLC table with 7Cx5400R~0.25MB. The default is 0.5MB.
  • MB
  • Set Maximum

Local Storage

  • Clearing local storage will remove all your saved servers, previously used server, editor content, window pane heights, chart defaults (axis types and formats), and last use date.
  • Clear local storage
